Popular American R&B singer, Jeremih has been hospitalized in Chicago after contracting COVID-19. The 33-year-old singer is currently in an Intensive Care Unit on a breathing ventilator, TMZ reports. It is, however, not clear how long he’s been hospitalized. Chance The Rapper, 50 Cent alongside other celebrities have since taken to social media to wish Jeremih recovery as he battles COVID-19. Chance on his Twitter page urged his fans to pray for Jeremih. His tweet read: “Please if you can take a second to pray for my friend Jeremih, he is like a brother to me and he is ill right now. “I believe in the healing power of Jesus so if you can for me please say a prayer over him.”